image_analysis.description: A photograph of the interior of a walk-in closet. The closet contains a shelf at the top with a white bag labeled 'EUROPEAN WHITE GOOSE' and folded white towels. Below the shelf is a hanging rod filled with numerous white garments on hangers, likely shirts or robes. To the right, there are two patterned robes with intricate gold and dark red/green designs. On the floor of the closet, several pairs of slippers are visible. The walls are a light tan or beige color, and the floor is carpeted with a patterned design.
image_analysis.layout: Interior shot of a closet viewed through an open doorway.

notes: The text 'EUROPEAN WHITE GOOSE' is printed on a storage bag on the top shelf. The alphanumeric string at the bottom right is a Bates stamp used for document identification in legal or investigative contexts.
